      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MOORAK SALLY (8) was in the minors two back (18.15) at this track but ran below best last time there, finishing 6th. Solid record here at the distance winning five races. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Better than last start and worth following up. TRUST DEED (2) hit the ground running and was prominent throughout but faded out of it when 6th at Warrnambool in a Bottom Up - Grade 5. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Key player if finds best. COMPTON BLUE (5) filled the minor placings four races on end before breaking through for a maiden win last time, scoring by 4 lengths (17.86) at this track. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Has hit winning form and can measure up again. HEART TO HARTLEY (4) with some luck can improve on an unplaced run last time here.",
